abstract_ssm: Seymour Posner (1925-1988) was a pro-labor New York State Assemblyman, who represented the 76th District in the Bronx.  He was actively involved with the Workman's Compensation Board, in addition to the Workers Defense League, Inc.  Posner was an admitted Socialist who joined the Democratic Socialist Organizing Committee during the late 1970s.  The papers and photos featured in Posner's collection mostly relate to his service as Assemblyman and his work with the Workman's Compensation Board.
